review.review_text: Sunday lunch on Father's day with hubby and baby. Hubby had slow cooked lamb shank with red wine jus, i had flat head tails n chips, and a kiddy porterhouse for bub. We drank the Pale Ale.  Jamieson brewery is a child friendly pub, with a huge deck, large dining room, and outdoor play area (including awesome air bouncer for safe jumping)!, all nestled in a super beautiful location.The restaurant was busy and fully booked when we went, so lucky we'd made a reservation. The ambiance, service and drinks were good (AMAZING pale ale) so it was a little sad that the food let them down. On the plus side the poterhouse was perfectly cooked and side salad delicious, on the minus, the shanks were a bit dry, veg not well cooked, and our chips came out cold.  Score out of 5: Food: 0.5 Drink: 0.9 Ambiance: 0.8 Service: 0.8 Price: 0.7  3.7 rounds up to 4.0

We were recommended to go check this place out. We travelled 40 minutes to get there from visiting family in the area. We were told that the kitchen was closed at 2pm and the bar assistant offered us toasties. After making the decision to have a toastie and a drink we were turned away from the owner who said that they were not serving food until 2:30pm (it was 2:17). He was so incredibly rude. No reasonable explanation. He walked from behind the bar and tapped at the A4 printed sheet on the wall ‚Äúwhat does this say, see it says 2:30‚Äù. He then went on to explain that they have to close because ‚Äúhe can‚Äôt have 10 staff on all day in the kitchen‚Äù. He was just so so rude. I haven‚Äôt experienced something like that before especially in a small country area where business would be tough. I think he should reconsider his approach.

restaurant.name: Earl's Secret

location.address: Oriental Buildings, Commissioners Road, Marlimund, Ooty

restaurant.timings: 8 AM to 10 AM, 7 PM to 10 PM, 12 Noon to 3:30 PM

review.review_text: Strictly average food (tried only Italian dishes not sure about North Indian dishes Nice concept and good atmosphere

We were looking for a place to dine which offers a great view in ooty. Found this place on Zomato and looking at the pics and reviews we decided to go there. We were mesmerised by the beauty of this place with all greenery around. Earl‚Äôs Secret located in King‚Äôs Cliff hotel, Ooty is considered one of the best places for Luxurious Fine Dining. It serves Continental, Mughlai and Chinese Cuisine. The USP of this place is its ambience. It offers indoor as well outdoor dining.Glasshouse on the lawn is the best place to have an awesome dining experience. We chose Glass house dining.  We ordered a variety of dishes  1.Roasted Mushroom soup- Average in taste 2.French onion soup- Average in Taste 3.Pasta Alfredo- It was just ok 4.Murgh Tikka Masala- Chicken was succulent and flavourful 5.Garlic Naan- This scored high on my tastebuds 6.Mango Panna cota- It was good 7.Earl‚Äôs secret brownie- This was the showstopper. Tasted awesome  This place scores high on ambience and hospitality but low on service. It was tad slow and there is a lot of scope for improvement   This place is highly recommend to everyone who is looking for an amazing dining experience and breathtaking view  Food - 3/5- more than average considering the town is very small and not that open to all types of cuisine   Ambience - 5/5  Hospitality - 5/5  Service - 2/5 - tad slow  Staffs - very courteous   N.B : This place is usually fully crowded during lunch and dinner. Unless you go early, it would be a long wait to get seated. And for Glasshouse particularly, the queue is longer.

We came here for a breakfast....amazing property.. Sad that we did not stay here.. their secret brownie was just perfect.... And staff is full of passion and energy.... Good job guys!!!  BUT the club sandwich and beef burger were below average and overpriced. Not worth it at all.

During my planning for Ooty trip, I was looking for local restaurants there, and I found this one quite interesting. Located at a high, seculated place Earl's Secret is the in house restaurant of King's Cliff Hotel.  Don't call it an ambience, the nature took care of it. They have three kind of seating arrangement - in the house, outer lawn and the greenhouse like glass house. In the peak season many complains of not having a seat early, long queue before they can get a seat.  However we got lucky as it was not a peak season, got a seat as fast as possible. The hospitality was really, really good. And don't call it food - it's heavenly. We took a chicken dish and beef steak - both are simply amazing.  Dessert part was a surprise to us. The blueberry puddling was so yumming that we repeated the order with mango variant.  It's a definitely WIR (Will I Return) restaurant!!

Beautiful location and ambience. Seating in the glass house is fantastic in cold weather!  Staff is friendly and helpful.  Food has good taste and presentation.  The coffee shop idea is nice.  Gets crowded so reach early.
